---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import LoopsDiagram from '../components/LoopsDiagram.astro';
import AltitudesDiagram from '../components/AltitudesDiagram.astro';
---
<Base>
  <h1>My Alicia</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    An AI teammate that collaborates with you on your learning journey,
    transforming knowledge into wisdom. My Alicia grows with you, learns
    from you, and adapts with you — as you do the same toward your own
    knowledge.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Humorphism</strong> is the design philosophy that seeks to
    replace the user interface built for operating tools with a
    <em>human interface</em> built for collaborating with AI teammates.
    My Alicia is what that looks like as code you can run on your own
    machine.
  </p>

  <p>
    My Alicia has an awareness layer that lets her develop her attention
    and way of being along with yours. She is open source and easy to set up.
  </p>

  <div class="figure">
    <LoopsDiagram />
    <p class="caption">Three depths of attention — Listen, Notice, Know — over a shared memory substrate.</p>
  </div>

  <p>
    What she works with is your knowledge — and she works with it
    in altitudes. Daily inputs metabolize into synthesis, synthesis
    into wisdom. External research keeps the loop open.
  </p>

  <div class="figure">
    <AltitudesDiagram />
    <p class="caption">From notes to wisdom — the altitudes of knowing.</p>
  </div>

  <hr class="rule" />

  <h2>For designers and builders</h2>

  <p>
    The contribution surface here is what we call <strong>awareness primitives</strong> —
    small, opinionated modules that turn some slice of life into structured
    memory the loops can metabolize. A reading-pattern primitive. A
    calendar-rhythm primitive. A relationship-graph primitive.
  </p>

  <p>
    Don't think of contributions as "writing code." Think of them as
    <em>designing perception</em>. Designing perception is what design
    practice needs to expand into in the agentic era.
  </p>

  <hr class="rule" />

  <h2>Try it</h2>

  <p>
    <code>pip install myalicia &amp;&amp; myalicia init</code>
  </p>

  <p>
    The init flow is more than configuration — it's a guided introduction
    to relationship-shaped AI. Each setup step is paired with a one-screen
    explanation of which loop it activates and why.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a class="cta" href="https://github.com/mrdaemoni/myalicia">View on GitHub →</a>
  </p>
</Base>
